A single lotus flower floating on perfectly still dark water, its delicate pink petals half-open, with one petal beginning to wilt while a fresh bud emerges beside it. The scene is rendered in Studio Ghibli style with soft watercolor textures, gentle gradients of twilight purple and rose gold reflecting on the water's surface. Tiny ripples spread outward in concentric circles, creating a sense of quiet movement. The composition is serene and contemplative, with muted earth tones and a dreamy atmospheric haze in the background suggesting distant misty mountains. The lighting is diffused and golden, evoking the liminal moment between day and night, perfectly balanced.
